---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Book"
  description="Work-in-progress book framing for the Verification Design pattern catalog."
  noindex={true}
>
  <div class="book-page">
    <h1>AI Design Patterns</h1>
    <p><em>Elements of Reusable Agentic Software.</em></p>

    <p>
      This site renders the catalog as a reference. The book framing
      collects the same material into a linear read with a foreword, parts,
      and a closing pattern language section. Work in progress.
    </p>

    <h2>Outline</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Part I. The New Forces.</li>
      <li>Part II. Context and State Patterns.</li>
      <li>Part III. Verification Patterns.</li>
      <li>Part IV. Orchestration Patterns.</li>
      <li>Part V. Pattern Languages.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      For now, read the
      <a href="/principles/">principles</a>
      and the
      <a href="/patterns/">patterns</a>
      directly.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
